      • initialize

        public void initialize​(java.net.URL url,
                       java.util.ResourceBundle rb)
        Sets up the scene GUI components utilizing the resource bundle for text values. Two lambda expressions is used to implement the ChangeListener interface and provide extra functionality for when users select items in the appTableView and to resize the daily contact schedule time bar so that it matches the width of its parent whenever the window is resized. Lambdas are also used to implement the Callback interface to assist with the formatting of table cells.
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
        Parameters:
        url - the url of the scene's fxml layout
        rb - the currently loaded resource bundle

      • populate

        void populate()
        Calls populate on both the appointment table, and the combo boxes. Also calls checkForUpcomingApp as that operation must be performed immediately after all initialization methods have run.

      • setupTable

      • populateTable

        void populateTable()
        Gets all appointment data from the Database class and uses it to populate the table view. A lambda expression is used to implement the Runnable interface and submit the task to the database to fetch the appointment records. Three more Runnable lambdas are nested inside to update GUI components on the JavaFX thread. A notification is displayed if the database request fails for any reason.

      • checkForUpcomingApp

        private void checkForUpcomingApp()
        Checks to see if the currently logged in user has an appointment scheduled within the next fifteen minutes. A lambda expression is used to implement the Runnable interface and submit the task to the database to fetch the appointment records. Three more Runnable lambdas are nested inside to update GUI components on the JavaFX thread. A notification is displayed indicating whether or not there is an upcoming appointment or if the database request fails for any reason. Lastly, Predicate and Comparable interfaces are implemented with lambda expressions in a stream used to filter the appointment list.

      • onActionTypeComboBox

        private void onActionTypeComboBox()
        Tries to activate the appConfirmBtn when a selection is made in the typeComboBox.

      • onKeyTypedAppField

        private void onKeyTypedAppField()
        Tries to activate the appConfirmBtn whenever a key is typed in any of the toolbar text fields.

      • onActionConfirm

        private void onActionConfirm()
        Gathers all the input data from the tool drawer elements and calls the relevant confirm method when the appConfirmBtn is pressed.

      • onActionRefresh

        private void onActionRefresh()
        Makes a request to the Database class to perform a COMMIT on the database. This deselects any selected items and closes the tool drawer. A lambda expression is used to implement the Runnable interface and submit a new task to the database to perform the COMMIT. Three more Runnable lambdas are nested inside to update GUI components on the JavaFX thread. A notification is displayed to report the success or failure of this request.

      • onActionAppMode

        private void onActionAppMode()
        Change how the appointments in the appTableView are filtered and displayed when the appModeBtn is pressed.
